Comment:
The debate last night between Trump and Harris seemed to highlight strong contrasts between the candidates. Supporters of Trump might argue that he showed confidence and adherence to his principles. On the other hand, Harris's supporters might view her performance as well-prepared and focused. Debates often evoke strong reactions, and how one interprets them can depend greatly on their political views and expectations. 
One thing to be sure is that the debate format was unfairly structured against Trump, the moderators were clearly biased, making it a three-on-one debate. 
Watch it yourself to determine the intelligence of each candidate and more importantly to determine which candidate truly cares for the country. 

In my opinion, to make the USA "great again," we need to truly focus on several key areas. First, boosting the economy is crucial, so we should create more jobs, drive innovation, and ensure fair trade practices. Addressing inflation is also critical; controlling rising prices will help maintain economic stability and ensure that everyday life remains affordable for all. Investing in education and skills training will help prepare people for the future workforce. We also need to make healthcare more accessible and affordable while strengthening public health. Updating our infrastructure and promoting green energy will help us move forward while taking care of the environment. Keeping the country safe with strong defense and robust cybersecurity is essential. We need transparent, accountable government and bipartisan cooperation to tackle major issues effectively. Addressing income inequality and supporting small businesses will help create a fairer society. Encouraging civic engagement and building community ties will foster unity, and we must address systemic issues to ensure justice and inclusivity for everyone. Finally but not the least important key, smart immigration policies and workforce development will support long-term stability. All of this requires a team effort from the government, businesses, and communities to make a real difference.
We should not focus on anything else!
